Description: Steinberger Spirit GT-Pro Standard Electric Guitar Steinberger Spirit GT-Pro Standard I don’t think they make this model anymore, with the single-coil in the neck position. This comes with the original Steinberger Spirit gig bag (dusty), tremolo arm, large and small adjustment allen wrenches, and a hard case that isn’t really a guitar case. The hard case is a Game Winner case for a take-down double barrel shotgun, but it works great for this guitar. I bought this a few years ago, to have a full-scale travel guitar, but it seems like I never have room to take a guitar with me or time to play it when I travel, so I have hardly used it. Condition: Excellent. Only noticeable scratch is on the back, near the strap button – may be a scratch of just a black scuff mark from something black rubbing across it. Plastic still on the rear cover plate. I have tested it to make sure there is no scratchiness in the pots or static in the switch – sounds like brand new. The manual with it is actually for a Steinberger Synapse and the 3 extra sets of string are years old (older than the guitar) so I wouldn’t count on them to be good replacements. The guitar is in great shape and plays and sounds great.
